GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 878
Short Title: Increased Academic Transparency. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Johnson, Blackwell, Gable, and Willis (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Education - K-12, if favorable, Judiciary 2, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and
Operations of the House
April 10, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE FOR INCREASED PUBLIC ACCESS TO LESSON PLANS AND
3 OTHER INSTRUCTIONAL MATERIALS IN PUBLIC SCHOOLS.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1.(a) Article 7B of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
6 adding a new Part to read:
7 "Part 7. Academic Transparency.
8 "§ 115C-76.75. Inform the public about course materials.
9 (a) The following definitions apply in this section:
10 (1) Action-oriented civics learning assignments or projects. – Assignments or
11 projects that require students to contact elected officials or advocate for a
12 political or social cause or to participate in political or social demonstrations.
13 (2) Course materials. – Any material used for instruction in a course, including,
14 but not limited to, all instructional materials, supplemental materials,
15 textbooks, other reading materials, videos, digital materials, websites, and
16 other online applications.
17 (3) Instructional materials. – Systematically organized material comprehensive
18 enough to cover the primary objectives outlined in the standard course of
19 study for a grade or course. Formats for instructional materials may be print
20 or nonprint, including hardbound books, softbound books, activity-oriented
21 programs, classroom kits, or digital resources that require the use of electronic
22 equipment in order to be used in the learning process.
23 (4) Lesson plan. – An outline of all of the following:
24 a. The instruction provided by a teacher for a course that includes a list
25 of (i) all course materials assigned, distributed, or otherwise presented
26 in the course and (ii) when students must select course materials from
27 a defined list, all course materials on that list.
28 b. Each grade- or school-wide presentation, assembly, lecture, or other
29 activity or event facilitated by the school during instructional hours
30 outside of an individual teacher's classroom, excluding student
31 presentations. The outline shall include a list of (i) each presenter by
32 name and organization and (ii) any course material used or presented.
33 (5) Supplemental materials. – Educational materials that supplement specific
34 instruction for the standard course of study selected and procured by a local
*H878-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 board of education for a grade or course or general education needs of the
2 school. Supplemental materials may include textbooks, library books,
3 periodicals, audiovisual materials, action-oriented civics learning assignments
4 or projects, and other supplemental instructional materials needed for
5 instructional purposes in the local school administrative unit. Supplemental
6 materials may be print or nonprint, including hardbound books, softbound
7 books, activity-oriented programs, classroom kits, or digital resources that
8 require the use of electronic equipment in order to be used in the learning
9 process.
10 (b) The governing body of a public school unit shall ensure that the following information
11 for each school it governs is prominently displayed on the school website, organized, at a
12 minimum, by subject area and grade level:
13 (1) All lesson plans used shall be posted online no later than 10 days after the
14 lesson was given. Lesson plans shall include the following, at a minimum:
15 a. The names of all instructional and supplemental materials used by the
16 school with an electronic link to the instructional materials website.
17 b. Any other course materials used in a course, organized by title, and the
18 author, organization, or website associated with each material and
19 activity. These course materials shall include materials created by the
20 teacher, with the teacher identified as the author. The lesson plan shall
21 include a brief descriptor of the course materials and a link to the
22 course material, if publicly available on the internet, or information on
23 how to request review of a copy of the course material in person.
24 Nothing in this section shall be construed to require the digital
25 reproduction or posting of copies of the course materials themselves.
26 (2) For all public school units, any procedures for the documentation, review, or
27 approval of the lesson plans, including course materials identified in those
28 plans, by the principal, curriculum administrators, or other teachers.
29 (3) For all public school units, the procedure established by the governing board
30 for requesting an in-person review of a course material not publicly available
31 on the internet.
32 (4) For all public school units, a list of teacher and staff training materials and
33 activities used at each school during the current school year.
34 (c) The governing body shall provide access from the website of the public school unit
35 to the information required by subsection (b) of this section at all times, either through a website
36 maintained by the public school unit or by a link to another website where the information is
37 publicly accessible. Public access to the information shall be maintained by the public school
38 unit for two calendar years from the date the material is posted. The Department of Public
39 Instruction shall make available to public school units one or more templates for providing
40 information as required by this section. A public school unit may exercise flexibility in
41 determining the most effective means of compliance with the requirements of this section,
42 including, but not limited to, utilizing any of the following in its discretion:
43 (1) Providing a template created by the Department of Public Instruction to
44 teachers to facilitate reporting of lesson plans.
45 (2) Creating one or more templates to provide to teachers to facilitate reporting of
46 lesson plans. The public school unit may customize templates for grades or
47 courses and may autopopulate any course materials required by the public
48 school unit as part of the curriculum for a particular grade or course.
49 (3) Allowing utilization of online collaborative software, documents, or
50 spreadsheets to allow multiple authorized users to update content.
Page 2 House Bill 878-First Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (4) To the extent allowable under the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act
2 (FERPA), 20 U.S.C. § 1232g, providing temporary login credentials via a
3 publicly accessible link on the school's website to the school's online learning
4 management system for any grade levels requested, provided that both of the
5 following apply:
6 a. All information required under this section is listed within the online
7 learning management system.
8 b. The login credentials are automatically generated immediately on
9 request and provide access for the requested grade levels for not less
10 than 72 hours at least once per 30-day period for each requestor. The
11 access provided via the login credentials may be limited to the
12 information required by this section and is not required to provide
13 access to academic assessments, answer keys, student generated
14 content, student performance records, or other student identifying
15 information.
16 (d) A governing body that is responsible for the operation of schools with fewer than 30
17 students cumulatively is not required to comply with the requirements of this section.
18 (e) For purposes of teacher privacy, a teacher or staff member may request that the school
19 use the teacher's or staff member's personal title and last initial rather than the teacher's or staff
20 member's full name when posting materials online to be viewed by the public."
21 SECTION 1.(b) Article 4 of Chapter 116 of the General Statutes is amended by
22 adding a new section to read:
23 "§ 116-69.3. Inform the public about course materials.
24 The Board of Trustees shall ensure that information about course materials is prominently
25 displayed on the website of the North Carolina School of the Arts for all elementary, middle, and
26 high school programs, in accordance with G.S. 115C-76.75."
27 SECTION 1.(c) G.S. 116-235 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
28 "(k) Course Materials. – The Board of Trustees shall ensure that information about course
29 materials is prominently displayed on the website of the School in accordance with
30 G.S. 115C-76.75."
31 SECTION 2. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
32 the 2025-2026 school year.
